POLICE in Rukwa Region have arrested a 50-year old woman for allegedly killing her husband, Katiluni Safi (58) after hitting him on the head. The Rukwa Regional Police Commander (RPC), Mr Justine Masonje told the ‘Daily News’ over the phone that the grisly incident happened shortly after mid –night of Friday at Kaengesa village. “The man returned home at 23:00 pm under the influence of alcohol and started annoying his wife by insulting her. She rushed to the kitchen and returned armed with a piece of wood with which she allegedly attacked her husband viciously, “ added the RPC. The regional boss said that the man sustained severe multiple injuries on his head and was rushed to Rukwa Regional Referral Hospital and died while receiving treatment. He said the woman will be taken to court after completion of investigations.